The paper focuses on developing a machine system that involves real-time robot vision, sensor fusion, and learning algorithms (reinforcement learning) for tasks such as obstacle avoidance, foraging, and predator-prey robot. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the use of learning algorithms and virtual environments suggests that the paper may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The involvement of robot vision and sensor fusion suggests that the paper may also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Finally, the use of reinforcement learning for a variety of tasks in unknown environments suggests that the paper may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
